# Formatting for the C++ validation harness, enforced by .github/workflows/clang-format.yml.
#
# The first four settings are upstream apache/arrow-adbc's .clang-format verbatim (minus its
# ASF license header, which does not apply here). Deliberately copied rather than tuned: this
# harness subclasses their DriverQuirks and is read side-by-side with their
# adbc_validation_*.cc, so matching their wrapping keeps the two diffable.
#
# ReflowComments is the one deviation. Upstream leaves it on (Google default), but our comments
# are long hand-wrapped prose — numbered lists, hanging indents, aligned continuations — and
# reflowing them to 90 columns mangles that structure without improving anything. Off means
# clang-format formats code and leaves comment prose alone.
#
# Scoped to this directory — clang-format walks up from each file, so nothing outside
# adbc-validation/ is affected.
---
BasedOnStyle: Google
ColumnLimit: 90
DerivePointerAlignment: false
IncludeBlocks: Preserve
ReflowComments: false
